The paper deals with a statistical hypothesis testing problem using nonparametric methods and focuses on the detection of anomalous data streams. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). The use of maximum mean discrepancy and reproducing kernel Hilbert space also suggests a connection to kernel methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and related fields.
